    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-01-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="572"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.60 a 11/6</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs of San Marino</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gozi</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-01-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1925</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have received the communication which
                    you did me the honor to address to me on November 19, 1924, stating the reasons
                    which have made it appear to the Government of San Marino necessary to establish
                    a Legation at Washington, and inquiring whether this course would be agreeable
                    to the Government of the United States.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to advise you that should it be the pleasure of the
                    Government of San Marino to accredit a diplomatic representative <pb facs="0788"
                        n="706" xml:id="pg_706"/> to the Government of the United States, the
                    President, appreciating the sentiments of friendship to which you give
                    expression, will be happy to receive him, and to accord him formal
                        recognition.<note n="4" xml:id="d572fn4">The files of the Department show no
                        further action regarding the establishment of a Legation of San Marino in
                        the United States.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E. Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
